### CSS 2D Transforms

**Transform** modifies an element's position, size, and rotation in 2D space.

---

### Transform Functions

| Function | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `translate(x, y)` | Move element | `translate(50px, 100px)` |
| `translateX(n)` | Move horizontally | `translateX(30px)` |
| `translateY(n)` | Move vertically | `translateY(-20px)` |
| `rotate(angle)` | Rotate | `rotate(45deg)` |
| `scale(x, y)` | Resize | `scale(1.5)` |
| `scaleX(n)` | Scale horizontally | `scaleX(2)` |
| `scaleY(n)` | Scale vertically | `scaleY(2)` |
| `skew(angleX, angleY)` | Skew | `skew(10deg, 5deg)` |
| `matrix(a,b,c,d,e,f)` | All in one | `matrix(1,0,0,1,50,50)` |

---

### Translate

```css
.element {
  transform: translate(50px, 100px);
  /* Moves 50px right, 100px down */
}

/* Perfect centering trick */
.center {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
}
```

---

### Rotate

```css
.element {
  transform: rotate(45deg);  /* Clockwise */
  transform: rotate(-90deg); /* Anti-clockwise */
  transform: rotate(1turn);  /* Full rotation */
}
```

---

### Scale

```css
.element {
  transform: scale(1.5);       /* 150% size */
  transform: scale(0.5);       /* 50% size */
  transform: scale(2, 0.5);    /* 2x wide, 0.5x tall */
}
```

---

### Skew

```css
.element {
  transform: skew(10deg);     /* 10deg horizontal tilt */
  transform: skew(-10deg, 5deg); /* X and Y skew */
}
```

---

### Multiple Transforms

```css
.element {
  transform: translate(50px, 20px) rotate(45deg) scale(1.2);
}
```

Order matters! Rightmost applies first.

---

### Transform Origin

```css
.element {
  transform-origin: center;        /* Default */
  transform-origin: top left;       /* From top-left corner */
  transform-origin: 20% 80%;       /* Custom position */
  transform-origin: 0 0;           /* Top-left in pixels */
}
```

---

### Performance Note

`transform` is **GPU-accelerated**. It's more performant than animating `margin`, `top`, `left`, or `width`.

```css
/* GOOD - GPU accelerated */
.element {
  transition: transform 0.3s ease;
}
.element:hover {
  transform: translateX(100px);
}

/* BAD - causes layout recalc */
.element {
  transition: margin-left 0.3s ease;
}
.element:hover {
  margin-left: 100px;
}
```

> **Best Practice:** Use `transform` for animations, not `margin`, `top`, `left` etc. It's smoother and GPU-accelerated.
